A '''daïra''' or '''daerah''' ({{Lang-ar|دائرة}} ''[[circle (country subdivision)|circle]]''; plural ''dawaïr'') is an [[administrative division]] in [[Algeria]] and [[Western Sahara]] in [[West Africa]], as well as [[Brunei]], [[Indonesia]] and [[Malaysia]] in [[Southeast Asia]]. It is commonly translated in [[English language|English]] as "[[district]]".

== West Africa ==
{{main|Districts of Algeria|Districts of Western Sahara}}
"Daïra" is the primary spelling variant used in Algeria and Western Sahara. It is a subdivision of [[wilayah]] in both countries.

== Southeast Asia ==
"Daerah" is an [[Arabic language|Arabic]] loanword in [[Malay language|Malay]] and [[Indonesian language|Indonesian]], which is cognate with "daïra".

=== Brunei ===
{{main|Districts of Brunei}}
A daerah or [[districts of Brunei|district]] is the primary [[subdivisions of Brunei|subdivision]] of [[Brunei]]. There are four {{lang|ms|daerah}}, namely [[Belait District|Belait]], [[Brunei-Muara District|Brunei-Muara]], [[Temburong District|Temburong]] and [[Tutong District|Tutong]]. A daerah is subdivided into [[mukims of Brunei|mukims]] (equivalent to subdistricts) and subsequently [[villages of Brunei|villages]] ({{lang|ms|kampung}}).

=== Indonesia ===
{{See also|Provinces of Indonesia}}
In [[Indonesia]], "daerah" is used as in the term {{lang|id|daerah istimewa}}, which refers to the [[Provinces of Indonesia|Special Regions]] or provinces with special status. There are five Special Regions, namely [[Aceh]], [[Jakarta]], [[Special Region of Yogyakarta]], [[Papua (province)|Papua]] and [[West Papua (province)|West Papua]].

=== Malaysia ===
{{main|Districts of Malaysia}}
A daerah or [[districts of Malaysia|district]] is a type of state administrative divisions in [[Malaysia]]. It is the primary subdivision of the [[states of Malaysia|states]] in [[Peninsular Malaysia]], where as in [[Sabah]] and [[Sarawak]] in [[Malaysian Borneo]], it is the secondary subdivision which is below [[divisions of Malaysia|divisions]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.statoids.com/ymy.html|title=Districts of Malaysia|website=statoids.com|access-date=29 August 2018}}</ref> Regardless, any daerah may be subdivided into [[mukims of Malaysia|mukim]].

