{{Infobox company
  |name     = Knowledge Oasis Muscat (KOM)
  |type     = Free Economic Zone
  |location_city    = Muscat, Al Rusayl
  |location_country = [[Oman]]
  |website = http://www.kom.om
}}

'''Knowledge Oasis Muscat''' (KOM) is a 20,000 square meter technology park located near [[Muscat International Airport]], [[Oman]]. KOM neighbours Rusayl Industrial Estate - the Sultanate's largest industrial park - and [[Sultan Qaboos University|SQU]]. For start-up companies that require a total support package, KOM created The Knowledge Mine (TKM) a business incubator program that offers tenants a combination of subsidized offices and utilities in addition to a variety of business support program services. KOM is also home to the [[MECIT|Middle East College]] and the Waljat Colleges of Applied Sciences. Currently, the KOM campus boasts an undergraduate population of approximately 3,000 students.

KOM was built to support technology-focussed [[Startup company|startup]] enterprises as well as corporate entities such as [[Ericsson]], [[Oracle Corporation]], [[Hewlett Packard]], [[Motorola]], [[Microsoft]], [[Oman TradaNet llc]], [[NCR Corporation|NCR]], [[Wipro Gulf LLC]] and [[Huawei]]. It also host Oman's [[Information Technology Authority|ITA]] which is the body that is responsible of managing the e-governance project in Oman.

