'''Kustošak''' is a stream passing through the neighbourhoods of [[Kustošija]] and [[Trešnjevka]] in [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]]. It is located on the western part of [[Medvednica]] Mountain's southern slope.<ref name="pp medvednica">{{cite web|title=Nature - Water|url=http://www.stari.pp-medvednica.hr/Medvednica_en/Medvednica_priroda_hidrologija_en.htm|website=Medvednica Nature Park|accessdate=18 May 2017}}</ref> The stream's upper basin is not easily accessible due to suburban development, but public walkways have been built along its lower basin. Before the urbanisation of Trešnjevka, Kustošak used to flow directly into [[Sava|Sava River]], but due to the river's [[meander]]ing only a sharp remains of the stream's former mouth. Further downstream, Kustošak discharges into the [[Vrapčak]] stream. Parts of the stream were covered in the course of the city's expansion,<ref name="h-alter zagreb's streams">{{cite web|last1=Šimpraga|first1=Saša|title=Perspektive gradskih potoka|url=http://www.h-alter.org/vijesti/perspektive-gradskih-potoka|website=H-Alter|accessdate=18 May 2017|language=hr|date=21 April 2016}}</ref> and several [[retention basin]]s have been built.<ref>{{cite web|title=Provedbeni plan obrane od poplava branjenog područja|url=http://www.voda.hr/sites/default/files/clanak/bp_14_-_provedbeni_plan_obrane_od_poplava.pdf|website=Hrvatske Vode|accessdate=18 May 2017|language=hr|date=March 2014}}</ref>
In May 2013 and March 2014, the stream was polluted by a fluorescent green liquid,<ref>{{cite web|title=Zašto je potok Kustošak bio jarko zeleno - tirkizne boje?|url=https://www.tportal.hr/vijesti/clanak/zasto-je-potok-kustosak-bio-jarko-zeleno-tirkizne-boje-20130517|work=[[HINA]]|publisher=Tportal.hr|language=hr|accessdate=18 May 2017|date=17 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Madunić|first1=Ines|title=Onečišćenje u Zagrebu: Potok Kustošak ponovno pozelenio|url=http://www.24sata.hr/reporteri/potok-kustosak-u-zagrebackoj-kustosiji-ponovno-pozelenio-358449|website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]]|accessdate=18 May 2017|language=hr|date=19 March 2014}}</ref> which caused a dying of [[frog]]s. The authorities determined that the cause of the 2013 discoloration was deliberate waste dumping.<ref>{{cite web|title=Istraga u tijeku: Tko je 'zazelenio' zagrebački potok Kustošak?|url=http://dnevnik.hr/vijesti/hrvatska/tko-je-zazelenio-zagrebacki-potok-kustosak---286858.html|website=Dnevnik.hr|accessdate=18 May 2017|language=hr-HR|date=17 May 2013}}</ref> The stream is listed as having category II water quality.<ref>{{cite web|title=Plan za zaštitu voda Grada Zagreba|url=http://www1.zagreb.hr/zagreb/slglasnik.nsf/7ffe63e8e69827b5c1257e1900276647/f1499bc402bb2116c1256dd5004fe3ac/$FILE/01-04%20Plan%20za%20za%C5%A1titu%20voda%20Grada%20Zagreba.doc|website=Zagreb.hr|publisher=City of Zagreb|accessdate=18 May 2017|language=hr|format=DOC|date=29 March 2001}}</ref> It is also classified as a water flow with a protective corridor.<ref>{{cite web|title=Odluka o donošenju Prostornog plana Parka prirode Medvednica|url=http://narodne-novine.nn.hr/clanci/sluzbeni/2014_07_89_1800.html|website=[[Narodne novine]]|accessdate=18 May 2017|language=hr|date=15 July 2014}}</ref>
