{{Infobox protected area | name = Norra Kvill National Park | alt_name = Norra Kvills nationalpark | iucn_category = II | photo = Norra Kvill Nationalpark.jpg | photo_width = 288 | photo_caption = | location = [[Kalmar County]], [[Sweden]] | nearest_city = | coords = {{coord|57|46|N|15|35|E|region:SE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | area_km2 = 1.14 | area_ref = <ref name="naturvårdsverket">{{cite web | title=Norra Kvill National Park | url=http://www.swedishepa.se/Enjoying-nature/Protected-areas/National-Parks/Norra-Kvill/ | publisher=[[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]] | accessdate=2009-02-26}}</ref> | established = 1927, extended 1989<ref name="naturvårdsverket" /> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]] | website = }} '''Norra Kvill''' is a small [[national park]] (established in 1927) near [[Vimmerby]] in [[Kalmar]] county, [[Småland]], southeastern [[Sweden]]. A few kilometers from the park is the [[Rumskulla oak]], Europe's largest [[Quercus robur|English oak]] with a circumference of about {{convert|14|m|ft|abbr=on}}. The oak is thought to be about 1 000 years old. {{Swedish National Parks|float=none}}
